---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  seo={{
    title: "About",
    description:
      "Orbit is a tech blog exploring the craft of building for the modern web — deep dives on JavaScript, TypeScript, Rust, CSS, accessibility, and performance.",
    canonicalURL: new URL("/about", Astro.site).href,
  }}
  showSidebar={false}
>
  <article class="about-page">
    <h1>About Orbit</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      Orbit is a tech blog about the craft of building for the modern web.
      We publish deep dives on JavaScript, TypeScript, Rust, CSS,
      accessibility, and web performance — the tools and techniques that
      shape how we build.
    </p>

    <hr class="hairline" />

    <section>
      <h2>What we write about</h2>
      <p>
        Every article on Orbit aims to go beyond the surface. We don't
        publish "10 tips" listicles or framework announcements. Instead, we
        explore the ideas behind the tools: why a pattern emerged, what
        trade-offs it makes, and when you should reach for something else.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our contributors are working engineers who write from experience.
        Maya Chen leads our JavaScript and TypeScript coverage, drawing on
        years of building large-scale frontend applications. Devon Okonkwo
        covers CSS, accessibility, and web platform fundamentals, bringing
        a designer's eye to engineering topics.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Our philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        We believe that good writing about technology should be:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Precise</strong> — code examples that actually run,
          claims backed by data or experience.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contextual</strong> — every tool and technique exists
          in a context. We explain the context, not just the syntax.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Enduring</strong> — we'd rather publish one article
          that's still relevant in three years than ten that are outdated
          in three months.
        </li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Technical details</h2>
      <p>
        Orbit is built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, a
        static site generator that ships zero JavaScript by default. We
        use Markdown for content authoring, Tailwind CSS for styling, and
        deploy as static HTML. The site supports light and dark themes via
        CSS custom properties and respects your operating system
        preference.
      </p>
      <p>
        All content is licensed under
        <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/">CC BY 4.0</a>.
        The source code is available on GitHub.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-page {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .about-page h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .lead {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    color: var(--color-muted);
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .about-page hr {
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .about-page section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .about-page h2 {
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .about-page ul {
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-page li {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
